Faith, honesty, grace, and compassion.

18
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,260
如果你没赢得金牌
I just don't want you to be disappointed

19
00:03:21,330 --> 00:03:23,760
你也不用沮丧
if you don't win it.

20
00:03:23,830 --> 00:03:25,430
你什么时候再去约会
When are you having another date?

21
00:03:25,530 --> 00:03:26,430
怎么了
Why?

22
00:03:26,540 --> 00:03:28,140
你很在意这事吗
Does it bother you when I date?

23
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:30,500
没有 我怎么会在意呢
No, why would it bother me?

24
00:03:30,570 --> 00:03:31,240
嘿
Hey.

25
00:03:31,340 --> 00:03:32,240
嘿 安琪拉姑姑
Hey, Aunt Angela.

26
00:03:32,340 --> 00:03:33,240
嘿
Hey.

27
00:03:33,340 --> 00:03:35,440
嘿 小甜熊
Hey, honey bear.

28
00:03:35,510 --> 00:03:36,580
我给你找了个妹子
I found your gal.

29
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:37,980
艾玛正和我聊我约会的事呢
Em and I were just talking about me dating.

30
00:03:38,050 --> 00:03:39,580
不是约会 是找到新保姆了
Not a date, I found you a nanny.

31
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:41,850
那不是我的任务吗
Wasn't that the assignment?

32
00:03:41,950 --> 00:03:43,220
我是说 新保姆
I- I mean, new babysitter.

33
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,420
我知道你不需要新保姆
I know you don't need a new nanny.

34
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,150
我也不需要临时保姆
I don't need a new babysitter, either.

35
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:47,850
太逊了
It's stupid.

36
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:50,120
她还在为莱薇娅难过
She's still upset about Miss Levia.

37
00:03:50,190 --> 00:03:51,890
你应该照顾我 安琪拉姑姑
You should babysit me, Aunt Angela.

38
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:53,230
那是我的荣幸 我的女王
It would be an honour, my queen,

39
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,000
但我的病人可能会反对
but I think my patients might object.

40
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,400
别担心 艾玛
Don't worry, Em.

41
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,930
我会找一个你喜欢的保姆
I'm gonna find you someone you like.

42
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:02,370
哦 她还说这个学期会再拿个金牌
Oh, she also says she's gonna win another award this semester.

43
00:04:02,440 --> 00:04:03,270
哦
Oh.

44
00:04:03,370 --> 00:04:04,910
她真有干劲啊
She's got drive.

45
00:04:04,970 --> 00:04:06,510
你该很兴奋吧
You should be thrilled.

46
00:04:06,610 --> 00:04:09,080
是吗 艾玛
Right, Emma?

47
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:11,380
艾玛
Emma?

48
00:04:11,450 --> 00:04:13,850
外面喷水池里有只死猫
There's a dead cat in the fountain.

49
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,870
别伤心
Don't be sad.

50
00:04:32,970 --> 00:04:35,140
可能事发迅疾
It probably happened very fast.

51
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,970
我觉得它不会感到痛苦
I don't think it felt a thing.

52
00:05:03,900 --> 00:05:05,770
啊 啊啊啊
Ah! Ahhh!!!

53
00:05:06,570 --> 00:05:08,000
冷静 各位
Calm down, everyone.

54
00:05:08,070 --> 00:05:11,270
我保证 它更加害怕你
I guarantee you it's more afraid of you than you are of it.

55
00:05:11,340 --> 00:05:12,670
艾玛·格罗斯曼
Emma Grossman!

56
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:36,300
谢谢你 艾玛
Thank you, Emma.

57
00:05:36,370 --> 00:05:38,170
不客气 埃利斯老师
You're welcome, Mrs. Ellis.

58
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:46,110
你怎么做到的
How did you do that?

59
00:05:46,180 --> 00:05:48,380
我们家后院有个蜂窝
We have a nest in our back yard.

60
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:52,380
我爸爸说黄蜂只有受到威胁才会攻击
My dad says wasps only attack when they feel threatened.

61
00:05:52,480 --> 00:05:54,410
这是它们的本能 麦洛
It's nature, Milo.

62
00:05:59,690 --> 00:06:01,020
但愿你不会对尘土过敏
I hope you're not allergic to dust.

63
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,460
这里可能不是开会的好地方
This probably isn't the best place in the house

64
00:06:02,520 --> 00:06:05,390
但是 我们开会的时间不多
to have a meeting but I'm on a deadline.

65
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,430
没事
No worries.

66
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:07,890
你什么工作都在这里做吗
Do you make everything here?

67
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,730
不 几乎都不会来这里
No, hardly anything anymore.

68
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:14,070
我有两个工厂 这里是刚刚创业的地方
I have two factories going but this is where it all began.

69
00:06:14,170 --> 00:06:15,670
厉害
Cool.

70
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:18,540
那说说你吧
So tell me about you.

71
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:20,810
简历上说你是职业滑雪运动员
Your resume says you were a professional snowboarder.

72
00:06:20,880 --> 00:06:23,480
对 直到我交叉韧带断了
Yep, right up until I blew out my ACL.

73
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:24,780
我不希望听到这个
I hate to hear that.

74
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,690
那样最好
It's for the best.

75
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:30,750
我深受打击 于是就试着做些安稳的工作
I still hit it hard, I just try to avoid the dangerous stuff.

76
00:06:30,850 --> 00:06:32,250
也对
Sure.

77
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,790
那你做保姆有五年了
So you've been a nanny for five years?

78
00:06:33,890 --> 00:06:34,960
是的
That's right.

79
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:35,990
看起来你挺喜欢这样
You seem to like it.

80
00:06:36,060 --> 00:06:37,090
我喜欢孩子
I love kids.

81
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,860
没有别的 他们都很单纯
There's no BS. They're not complicated.

82
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:39,830
如果他们伤心了 就会哭
If they're sad, they cry.

83
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:41,090
倘若他们开心了 就会笑
If they're happy, they laugh.

84
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,260
惹人喜欢
It's refreshing.

85
00:06:42,330 --> 00:06:43,900
那还有别的事我需要了解的吗
So is there anything else I need to know?

86
00:06:43,970 --> 00:06:46,030
你的推荐人好像都很喜欢你
Your references all seem to love you.

87
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,330
烤奶酪是我的拿手
I make a mean grilled cheese.

88
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:49,240
你想知道秘密配方吗
You want to know the secret ingredients?

89
00:06:49,340 --> 00:06:50,240
好啊
Sure.

90
00:06:50,310 --> 00:06:51,140
腌菜和芥末
Pickles and mustard.

91
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:54,440
嘣 完成
Boom. Done.

92
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:57,480
那么 呃 你下周就开始工作吗
Well, uh... can you start next week?

93
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:59,010
艾玛就快放假了
Emma's about to begin her spring break.

94
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:00,610
当然 你想什么时候开始我就...
Sure. I can start whenever you need-

95
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,850
呃 格罗斯曼先生
Uh, Mr. Grossman?

96
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,080
这是昙花计划
Here are the steagle plans,

97
00:07:03,150 --> 00:07:05,190
在五分钟后你会有一个关于材料的电话
and you have a materials call in five minutes.

98
00:07:09,090 --> 00:07:09,690
谢谢
Thank you.

99
00:07:09,790 --> 00:07:10,520
还有想说的吗
Is there anything else?

100
00:07:10,630 --> 00:07:12,390
没有了
Nope.

101
00:07:13,930 --> 00:07:15,400
你还有什么问题吗
Is there anything you want to ask me?

102
00:07:15,460 --> 00:07:17,960
你女儿她性格怎么样
What's your daughter like?

103
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:22,200
艾玛她...做事很专心
Emma is... very focused.

104
00:07:22,270 --> 00:07:25,640
虽然只是个小女孩 但她总是能专心做事
She's a normal little girl, but she can be very focused.

105
00:07:25,710 --> 00:07:27,210
我都不知道如何形容了
I don't know how else to say it.

106
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:32,010
她很聪明 成绩全优 从没惹过麻烦
She's smart, straight A's, never gets into trouble...

107
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:33,510
喜欢热巧克力
loves hot chocolate.

108
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:34,610
是个乖女孩
My kinda girl.

109
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,680
我也觉得
Mine, too.

110
00:07:35,780 --> 00:07:36,750
你的妻子呢
And your wife?

111
00:07:36,820 --> 00:07:38,150
我能和她见见面吗
Should I meet with her, too?

112
00:07:38,220 --> 00:07:40,650
她在艾玛出生后就去世了
She died just after Emma was born.

113
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,420
我深表同情
I'm so sorry.

114
00:07:42,490 --> 00:07:43,860
谢谢
Thanks.

115
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:49,430
所以 就我们两人相依为命 互相照顾
So it's uh, it's just the two of us and um... we manage.

116
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:55,570
那么 我们下周见
Well, I guess I will see you next week.

117
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,140
我很期待
Looking forward to it.

118
00:08:03,010 --> 00:08:04,540
你手表酷毙了
Your watch is sick.

119
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:05,350
是吗
Right?

120
00:08:05,450 --> 00:08:06,480
这是我的生日礼物
I got it for my birthday.

121
00:08:06,550 --> 00:08:07,780
我生日时也收到过手表
I got a watch for my birthday too.

122
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:09,350
但我不怎么戴
I don't really wear it.

123
00:08:11,790 --> 00:08:12,690
小心点
Careful there!

124
00:08:12,790 --> 00:08:14,150
到你抓了
You're it!

125
00:08:18,930 --> 00:08:20,730
凯蒂 你还好吗
Katie, are you alright?

126
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:22,260
你还好吗
Are you ok?

127
00:08:23,270 --> 00:08:25,930
抱歉 我不是故意的
I'm so sorry, I didn't mean to hurt you.

128
00:08:26,030 --> 00:08:28,300
来 我扶你起来
Here, let me help you up.

129
00:08:29,770 --> 00:08:30,740
对不起
I'm so sorry.

130
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:34,540
到谁抓了
Who's it?

131
00:08:34,610 --> 00:08:36,110
还是你 快跑
You're still it, let's go!

132
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:02,470
瞧我给你带来了什么
I brought you your favourite.

133
00:09:02,570 --> 00:09:04,170
谢谢 爸爸
Thanks, daddy.

134
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:08,240
需要我指导吗
You want to read together?

135
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:10,040
不用了 爸爸
We don't have to, daddy.

136
00:09:10,110 --> 00:09:12,380
我知道你很忙
I know how busy you are.

137
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,380
如果我给你个拥抱 你会给我什么
What would you give me for a basket of hugs?

138
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:16,150
给你一个吻
A basket of kisses.

139
00:09:32,870 --> 00:09:35,140
给你一个吻
A basket of kisses.

140
00:09:38,410 --> 00:09:41,410
给你一个吻 给你一个吻
A basket of kisses. A basket of kisses.

141
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,110
给你一个吻
A basket of kisses.

142
00:09:43,210 --> 00:09:45,250
给你一个吻
A basket of kisses.

143
00:10:01,500 --> 00:10:04,300
你看起来真像个小明星
You look like a movie star.

144
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,730
别让我迟到了 爸爸
Don't make me late, dad.

145
00:10:05,830 --> 00:10:07,000
不会的
I won't.

146
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:03,220
礼服不错 麦洛
Nice suit, Milo.

147
00:11:03,330 --> 00:11:04,460
谢谢
Thanks.

148
00:11:04,530 --> 00:11:06,390
他一直盼望着这一天的到来呢
He has been counting down the days.

149
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:08,400
哦 可不是吗
Oh, tell me about it.

150
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,560
现在是颁奖时刻
And now, our final award.

151
00:11:10,630 --> 00:11:13,270
圣奥尔登奖章
The St. Alden's Citizenship Medallion.

152
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:16,470
每年我们都会颁给一位最有个性的
Every year we honour someone of character.

153
00:11:16,540 --> 00:11:18,670
一位真正代表着
Someone who truly embodies the values

154
00:11:18,740 --> 00:11:20,940
学校价值观的人
that this school was founded on.

155
00:11:21,010 --> 00:11:23,740
今年我很荣幸将
This year I am proud to award

156
00:11:23,810 --> 00:11:27,880
圣奥尔登奖章颁发给麦洛·柯蒂斯
the St. Alden's Citizenship Medallion to Milo Curtis.

157
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:37,460
你真棒
Good job.

158
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:49,300
给你 麦洛 你真棒
Here you go, Milo. Good job.

159
00:11:49,370 --> 00:11:50,870
谢谢
Thanks!

160
00:11:57,110 --> 00:11:58,850
哇
Wow!

161
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:00,650
很抱歉我错过了家长会
I'm sorry I missed your parent-teacher conference,

162
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:02,750
我在城里有个重要的工程
I had a big installation in the city.

163
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:05,150
别担心 我们可以改时间
No worries. We can reschedule.

164
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:06,350
艾玛表现得如何
How is Emma doing?

165
00:12:06,420 --> 00:12:08,150
我并不想为难你
I mean, not to put you on the spot.

166
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:09,060
嗯
Right.

167
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,020
她挺好的
She's fine.

168
00:12:10,090 --> 00:12:12,860
她 呃 我得说
She's um... I have to say,

169
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,590
我教书20年
I've never met anyone quite like her

170
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:17,160
从没见过像她这样的孩子
in my 20 years of teaching.

171
00:12:17,230 --> 00:12:18,770
为什么听起来像是件坏事
Why does that sound like a bad thing?

172
00:12:18,870 --> 00:12:21,600
不 我没有那个意思
No, I didn't mean that in any fashion at all.

173
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:23,200
艾玛她有很多优点
Emma's never had one mark against her

174
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:24,870
而且她还是班上的优等生
and she's one of our top students.

175
00:12:24,940 --> 00:12:27,110
她都可以当班长了
She can be a real leader when she wants to be.

176
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:28,780
但是呢
But?

177
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:30,840
她活在自己独特的世界里
Emma lives in her own particular world

178
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:33,210
但是那世界不是像
and I'm sure it isn't anything like the world

179
00:12:33,280 --> 00:12:34,750
你我活着的这个世界一样
that you and I live in.

180
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,650
我是说 她拥有许多对孩子来说
I mean, she has many remarkable qualities

181
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:38,420
非常优秀的卓越品质
that are great in a child.

182
00:12:38,490 --> 00:12:41,650
她的勇气是最难得的
Her courage is most unusual.

183
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:45,490
她没有任何生理恐惧
She's almost without any physical fear.

184
00:12:45,560 --> 00:12:47,830
而且必要时她能给人留下深刻的印象
And she really knows how to come across when she has to.

185
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,360
我打赌她能成为一名演员
She can be an actress, I bet.

186
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:51,400
算了吧 演员就算了
Please, not an actress.

187
00:12:51,470 --> 00:12:52,200
好吧
Alright.

188
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:53,170
埃利斯老师
Mrs. Ellis.

189
00:12:53,170 --> 00:12:54,000
噢 嗨 失陪了
Oh, hi. Excuse me.

190
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,600
好吧
Sure.

191
00:13:01,410 --> 00:13:03,680
我真替你骄傲 小甜熊 我知道你很失望
I'm proud of you, honey bear. I know you're disappointed.

192
00:13:03,750 --> 00:13:06,480
那奖牌本来应该属于我
That medal's mine. I deserve it.

193
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:08,180
麦洛甚至都不敢当着全班的面说话
Milo can't even talk in front of the class.

194
00:13:08,280 --> 00:13:10,450
艾玛
Emma.

195
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,690
每个人都有他们的特长
Everybody has something special to offer.

196
00:13:12,790 --> 00:13:14,320
麦洛是个好孩子
Milo's a good kid.

197
00:13:14,420 --> 00:13:15,490
是吗
Yeah?

198
00:13:15,560 --> 00:13:17,120
但他就是个糟糕的演讲者
Well, he's an awful public speaker.

199
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:18,160
他连拼写都不会
And he can't spell.

200
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:19,560
艾玛
Emma.

201
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:24,230
你说的对
You're right.

202
00:13:24,330 --> 00:13:26,330
对不起
Sorry.

203
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:28,540
麦洛是我的朋友
Milo's my friend.

204
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,540
我很开心他赢得了奖牌
I'm really happy he got it.

205
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:17,980
被你说对了 这里简直太酷了
You're right, this place is cool!

206
00:14:29,970 --> 00:14:31,930
我们应该回去了
We should go back now.

207
00:14:42,710 --> 00:14:44,480
艾玛 你怎么了
Emma, what's wrong?

208
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,710
你想干嘛
What do you want?

209
00:14:52,490 --> 00:14:54,650
你应该知道我要干嘛
I think you know.

210
00:15:06,430 --> 00:15:07,800
一二三
One, two, three.

211
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,970
不错 我会发邮箱给你的
That's good, I'll email it to you.

212
00:15:10,070 --> 00:15:12,140
嘿 爸 我们能回家了吗
Hey dad, can we get going?

213
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,140
当然
Sure.

214
00:15:13,240 --> 00:15:14,410
你知道麦洛去哪了吗
Has anyone seen Milo?

215
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:15,280
我没看到他
I haven't seen him.

216
00:15:15,340 --> 00:15:16,980
艾玛 你见到他了吗
Emma, have you seen him?

217
00:15:17,050 --> 00:15:19,380
呃 之前看到他是在篝火那里
Um, the last place I saw him was by the bonfire.

218
00:15:21,320 --> 00:15:23,180
救命啊 救命啊
Help! Help!

219
00:15:23,990 --> 00:15:25,520
快点
Quickly!

220
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,510
哦 我的天哪
Oh my god!

221
00:15:46,610 --> 00:15:48,510
麦洛 麦洛
MiloMilo?

222
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:52,180
醒醒 醒醒 宝贝 醒醒啊
Come on, come on, baby! Breathe!

223
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:54,350
快帮帮我们
Somebody do something!

224
00:15:54,450 --> 00:15:55,950
打报警电话
Call 911!

225
00:15:56,050 --> 00:15:57,320
麦洛
Milo!

226
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:59,990
醒醒 麦洛 醒醒
Come on, Milo. Come on.

227
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:03,760
麦洛
Milo?

228
00:16:06,700 --> 00:16:08,430
快救救孩子
Somebody help us!

229
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:12,000
可怜的孩子
That poor kid.

230
00:16:12,070 --> 00:16:13,700
在他们来抬走他之前
He was lying there on the rocks for hours

231
00:16:13,770 --> 00:16:16,270
他在岩石上躺了几个小时
before they came and took him away.

232
00:16:16,370 --> 00:16:19,340
太可怕了
It was horrible.

233
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,970
她还好吗
How is she?

234
00:16:21,080 --> 00:16:23,180
她还好
She's ok.

235
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,010
她应该是受到惊吓了
I think she's in shock.

236
00:16:25,010 --> 00:16:26,510
我们都被吓到了
I think we all are.

237
00:16:26,580 --> 00:16:28,110
她在楼上看书
She's up in her room, reading.

238
00:16:28,220 --> 00:16:30,250
这件事可能会成为她的阴影
I'm sure it'll hit her later.

239
00:16:30,350 --> 00:16:32,650
嗯 但愿不会这样
Yes, I'm sure it will.

240
00:17:05,150 --> 00:17:06,220
艾玛
Emma.

241
00:17:06,320 --> 00:17:07,450
早上好 爸爸
Morning, dad.

242
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,920
早上好 亲爱的
Morning, hon.

243
00:17:08,990 --> 00:17:10,220
你要麦片吗
Do you want some cereal?

244
00:17:10,290 --> 00:17:11,860
还有剩的
There's just enough left.

245
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:14,790
不用了 谢谢
No, I'm ok, thanks.

246
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:16,530
你感觉怎么样
How are you feeling?

247
00:17:16,630 --> 00:17:19,300
我很好
I'm alright.

248
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,230
希望今天不会下雨
I hope it doesn't rain today.

249
00:17:21,340 --> 00:17:23,740
我是说昨天的事
I meant about yesterday.

250
00:17:23,810 --> 00:17:25,570
你一定很难过吧
You must be pretty sad, right?

251
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:28,780
如果你想倾诉 我会听你说的
If you want to talk about it I'm here for you.

252
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,910
好啊
Ok.

253
00:17:30,980 --> 00:17:33,080
你想和我谈谈吗
Do you need someone to talk to?

254
00:17:35,580 --> 00:17:38,680
我不觉得有什么好谈的
I don't really think there's anything to talk about.

255
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:49,860
给她点时间 孩子的处理方法不同
Give her time. Kids process differently.

256
00:17:49,930 --> 00:17:52,500
别让她为难
Don't make her feel self-conscious.

257
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:54,100
你可能是对的
You're probably right.

258
00:17:54,170 --> 00:17:56,300
她就是很要强 知道吗
She's just so strong, you know?

259
00:17:56,370 --> 00:17:58,970
我是说 她的老师都这么说
I mean, even her teachers were talking about it.

260
00:17:59,040 --> 00:18:05,410
我只是希望她能花点时间...然后
I just hope that she can take some time and... feel.

261
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:08,150
瞧瞧是谁来了
Look who's here.

262
00:18:09,580 --> 00:18:10,580
顺便说一句 干得好
Great job, by the way.

263
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:11,620
她看起来很不错
She seems perfect.

264
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,620
米勒说她和萨姆相处得很好
Miller said she was great with Sam.

265
00:18:13,690 --> 00:18:15,190
我就是专业猎人
Professional head hunter, that's me.

266
00:18:15,290 --> 00:18:16,590
你是想约我朋友利兹出去吗
Are you gonna finally take my friend Lizzy out?

267
00:18:16,660 --> 00:18:17,890
哦老天 你真是没完没了啊
Oh my god, you are relentless.

268
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,330
没错 我会约她的
Yes, I will call her.

269
00:18:19,430 --> 00:18:20,730
嘿 你好
Hey there.

270
00:18:20,800 --> 00:18:22,800
我的任务是什么
Let's get this party started.

271
00:18:30,710 --> 00:18:33,340
这是洗衣机 这是干衣机
Washer, dryer, obviously.

272
00:18:33,410 --> 00:18:35,070
哇 这里太棒了
Wow, this place is amazing.

273
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,240
谢谢
Thanks.

274
00:18:36,310 --> 00:18:37,880
是艾玛出生前
It was a fixer-upper my wife and I bought

275
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,410
妻子和我买的旧房子
right before Emma was born.

276
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:40,980
这是你妻子吗
Was this your wife?

277
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:42,280
哦 没错
Oh, yeah.

278
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:44,950
那是某一年的圣诞贺卡
That was our Christmas card one year.

279
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:47,490
她来了
There she is.

280
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:48,550
艾玛 这是克洛伊
Emma, this is Chloe.

281
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,690
克洛伊 这是艾玛
Chloe, this is Emma.

282
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:50,990
嗨 艾玛
Hi Emma.

283
00:18:51,060 --> 00:18:52,660
很高兴见到你
It's very nice to meet you.

284
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:54,230
你的项链不错
I like your necklace.

285
00:18:54,330 --> 00:18:56,200
你想看看我的奖牌吗
Do you want to see my medals?

286
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,200
我们得先参观完房子
We have to finish the tour first.

287
00:18:58,270 --> 00:19:00,270
好了 这是紧急报警器
Anyway, emergency numbers here,

288
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:04,200
所有的钥匙都放在那个小地方
all the keys go in that uh, little place there.

289
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:06,540
呃 灭火器在洗涤槽的下面
Um, fire extinguisher is under the sink.

290
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:09,110
楼上卧室也有几个...
We have a couple upstairs in the bedrooms...

291
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:42,510
我想看电影
I wanna watch a movie.

292
00:19:42,580 --> 00:19:45,140
风吹开了窗户
The wind was blowing a window open.

293
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:47,180
我关好窗就下来
I'll be down in a minute.

294
00:20:18,150 --> 00:20:24,350
电视播出的影片为《百纳衣到华服》 由孩子们扮演大人

295
00:20:20,350 --> 00:20:22,010
艾尔玛
Elmer!

296
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:23,680
奈儿
Nell!

297
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:30,290
看不懂 这太蠢了
I don't get it. This is stupid.

298
00:20:30,390 --> 00:20:31,620
什么蠢
What's stupid?

299
00:20:31,730 --> 00:20:35,600
秀兰·邓波儿
Shirley Temple.

300
00:20:35,660 --> 00:20:38,630
她可是一名美国大使
The woman was a United States ambassador.

301
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:42,770
不敢想象她有多蠢
I can't imagine she was very stupid.

302
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:44,700
我是说电影
I meant the movie.

303
00:20:48,940 --> 00:20:50,580
爸爸什么时候回来
When's my dad coming home?

304
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,810
快了
Soon.

305
00:20:51,910 --> 00:20:54,680
他在开会
He has a meeting.

306
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:57,320
你会为那个溺水的孩子伤心吗
So are you sad about the kid that drowned?

307
00:20:57,390 --> 00:20:59,420
我伤不伤心没什么关系
I don't think it matters if I'm sad.

308
00:20:59,490 --> 00:21:01,890
反正他都死了
He's dead, anyway.

309
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:06,330
况且 爸爸说我看到他溺水的时候面无表情
Besides, my dad said you don't feel anything when you drown

310
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:09,430
那你真是无忧无虑 是吧
You're all warm and fuzzy, aren't you?

311
00:21:09,530 --> 00:21:10,930
那你喜欢些什么
So what're you into?

312
00:21:11,030 --> 00:21:11,900
音乐
Music?

313
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:12,870
骑马
Horses?

314
00:21:12,970 --> 00:21:15,030
我都喜欢
I'm into everything.

315
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:17,300
你爸怎么样 有女朋友吗
What's the deal with your dadGot a girlfriend?

316
00:21:17,370 --> 00:21:19,840
没有 怎么了
No. Why?

317
00:21:19,910 --> 00:21:21,940
就问问 没什么大不了
Just asking, no biggie.

318
00:21:25,650 --> 00:21:28,280
他有段时间交过一个
He had one for a while.

319
00:21:28,380 --> 00:21:29,780
我不喜欢她
I didn't like her.

320
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:31,180
所以你爸甩了她吗
So he dumped her?

321
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,320
嗯
Yep.

322
00:21:33,390 --> 00:21:35,760
你真是个让我捉摸不透的人啊
You're sorta something else, aren't you?

323
00:21:35,860 --> 00:21:37,590
那你就是个小偷
And you're sort of a thief.

324
00:21:37,660 --> 00:21:39,790
你在说什么
Excuse me?

325
00:21:39,860 --> 00:21:41,260
而且还挺聪明
And you're smart.

326
00:21:41,330 --> 00:21:45,600
我刚看见你从我爸爸卧室拿走了药
I saw you take the pills from my dad's bedroom.

327
00:21:45,670 --> 00:21:50,140
但是又不足以让我爸爸注意到
But not enough for my dad to notice.

328
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:55,210
别担心 我不会说的
Don't worry, I won't tell.

329
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:59,450
我想我今晚就不用按时睡觉了
I think I'm gonna stay up past my bedtime tonight.

330
00:21:59,510 --> 00:22:03,080
你现在去给我拿点冰淇淋
Now go and get me some ice cream.

331
00:22:03,180 --> 00:22:05,480
你个小婊子
You little bitch.

332
00:22:11,860 --> 00:22:15,130
顺便再给我拿点饼干
And bring me a couple of cookies while you're at it.

333
00:22:43,020 --> 00:22:44,660
没事了
It's okay.

334
00:22:50,330 --> 00:22:52,500
谢谢
Thank you.

335
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,630
我深表遗憾
I'm so sorry.

336
00:22:53,740 --> 00:22:55,230
谢谢
Thank you.

337
00:22:56,700 --> 00:22:58,940
感谢到来
Thanks for coming.

338
00:22:59,040 --> 00:23:00,610
嘿 艾玛
Hi, Emma.

339
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:06,110
噢 别问我怎么样了
Oh, don't ask me how I am.

340
00:23:06,210 --> 00:23:07,780
我不想骗你
I don't wanna lie to you.

341
00:23:07,850 --> 00:23:10,450
仪式很棒
It was a beautiful service.

342
00:23:10,520 --> 00:23:12,550
他也度过了他的最后一日
He had a good last day.

343
00:23:12,620 --> 00:23:13,920
一个非常好的日子
A really good last day.

344
00:23:13,990 --> 00:23:16,020
我是说 他以前从未赢过什么
I mean, he has never won anything before

345
00:23:16,090 --> 00:23:18,960
而他对那奖牌感到特别骄傲
and he was so proud of that medal.

346
00:23:19,060 --> 00:23:21,390
我只想知道那奖牌哪里去了
I just wish I knew where it was.

347
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:24,000
你没有拿到奖牌吗
You don't have the medal?

348
00:23:24,100 --> 00:23:27,700
呃 可能是沉入海底了吧
Well, I think maybe it sunk to the bottom.

349
00:23:27,770 --> 00:23:29,000
我能为你做些什么吗
Is there anything I can do for you?

350
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:31,770
我想要一些他那天的照片
If you have any pictures of that day I'd like them.

351
00:23:31,840 --> 00:23:35,370
一些他开心的照片
Pictures of him playing, happy.

352
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:37,040
这算最好的帮助了
It really does help.

353
00:24:19,450 --> 00:24:21,620
爸爸
Dad?

354
00:24:21,690 --> 00:24:23,420
你在我房间干什么
What're you doing in my room?

355
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,520
就收拾一下
Just picking up a little.

356
00:24:24,630 --> 00:24:26,890
但这里很整齐
It is picked up.

357
00:24:26,990 --> 00:24:28,990
一直都很整齐
It's always picked up.

358
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:34,870
还有事吗
Anything else?

359
00:24:34,970 --> 00:24:36,600
没了
No.

360
00:25:13,910 --> 00:25:16,640
埃利斯老师
Miss Ellis.

361
00:25:16,740 --> 00:25:17,980
很高兴见到你
It's nice to meet you.

362
00:25:18,050 --> 00:25:19,580
相信我 我们建校95年来
Believe me, nothing like this has ever happened

363
00:25:19,650 --> 00:25:21,510
从未发生过这种事
in our 95-year history

364
00:25:21,620 --> 00:25:23,350
而我们调用了手头上的一切资源
and we're using every resource we have

365
00:25:23,420 --> 00:25:25,450
确保这种事不会再发生
to make sure that it never happens again.

366
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,950
但是有些法律问题我们必须处理下
But there is a legal issue that we have to contend with.

367
00:25:28,020 --> 00:25:29,260
请便
Sure.

368
00:25:29,320 --> 00:25:30,620
我们联系了所有的家长
We're reaching out to all the parents to gather

369
00:25:30,690 --> 00:25:32,860
收集一切能收集到的情报
whatever information we can.

370
00:25:32,930 --> 00:25:34,860
呃 好吧 我 我听不太懂
Well, ok, I- I don't really understand.

371
00:25:34,930 --> 00:25:36,860
所以这是保险之类的 还是...
So this is an insurance thing, or...?

372
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:39,230
没错 那是其中之一
That's one component, yes.

373
00:25:39,330 --> 00:25:41,100
那么 究竟发生了什么
Well, what did happen?

374
00:25:41,170 --> 00:25:42,800
也没人和大家说具体情况
No one's given anybody an update.

375
00:25:42,870 --> 00:25:44,240
麦洛怎么摔下悬崖的
How did Milo fall off that cliff?

376
00:25:44,340 --> 00:25:46,810
这就是我们想弄清楚的
That's what we're gonna find out.

377
00:25:46,870 --> 00:25:48,810
有警察介入吗
Are the police involved?

378
00:25:48,910 --> 00:25:51,310
我们无权透露
We're not at liberty to share that.

379
00:25:51,380 --> 00:25:54,650
显然 如果警察介入调查时
Obviously, if and when the authorities are involved,

380
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,420
有些家庭可能会不得安宁
we may share that information with the families.

381
00:25:56,480 --> 00:25:57,780
有些家庭
Some families.

382
00:25:57,850 --> 00:26:00,490
抱歉 你们是不是有什么瞒着我
Excuse me, but is there something you're not telling me?

383
00:26:00,560 --> 00:26:02,050
请别误会
Please don't misunderstand.

384
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:04,420
我们只是想得到事情的真相
We're just trying to get to the facts.

385
00:26:04,430 --> 00:26:07,930
但是我们必须知道艾玛听见或看见了什么
But if Emma heard or saw something, we need to know.

386
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:10,660
那男孩不会游泳 他还怕水
That boy couldn't swim and he was afraid of water.

387
00:26:10,730 --> 00:26:12,800
他为什么要去海岸岩壁上面
Why was he out on the rocks?

388
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:14,330
你个小混球
You little shit.

389
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:15,770
艾玛是最后一个见过那男孩的
Any information would be helpful

390
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:19,640
她知道的消息对我们有很大帮助
as it seems Emma was the last to see the boy.

391
00:26:19,740 --> 00:26:21,710
你说什么
I'm sorry?

392
